# LLM-as-judge config for the reply-drafter role. Rename to ``judge.yaml`` to enable.
#
# A drafted reply is free-text — wording varies every run, so exact-match
# scoring is wrong. This rubric scores whether the draft serves the requested
# intent in the requested tone, ready to send.
#
# Cross-family: the agent runs on openai by default, so the judge must NOT
# also run on openai (the eval engine refuses to let a provider judge itself).

method: llm_judge

model:
  provider: anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6
  params:
    temperature: 0.0

rubric: |
  Score the actual draft against the expected one for a reply-drafter.
    * Intent — does the draft_body accomplish the requested intent?
    * Tone — does it match the requested tone?
    * Send-ready — no placeholders, no hallucinated commitments; the
      suggested_next_actions are sensible follow-ups.

    1.0 = correct intent, right tone, send-ready, sensible next actions
    0.5 = on-intent but off-tone or leaves a soft placeholder
    0.0 = wrong intent, hallucinated commitments, or unusable placeholders

threshold: 0.7
